1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,451
Suggestions come slowly at first.

2
00:00:02,640 --> 00:00:09,970
Someone hesitantly says something like, well, you might cut down crime if you established more youth centers.

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:18,371
Before long, the group, which ten minutes ago was solidly against the idea, now begins to work up real enthusiasm.

4
00:00:18,720 --> 00:00:20,530
Work to eliminate poverty.

5
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:23,811
Most crime stems from the low income levels.

6
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:28,851
Conduct research to spot potential criminals before they commit a crime.

7
00:00:29,201 --> 00:00:33,171
Develop surgical procedures to cure some kinds of criminals.

8
00:00:33,441 --> 00:00:38,051
Educate law enforcement personnel in positive methods of reform.

9
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:47,571
These are just samples of the 78 specific ideas I've tabulated that could help accomplish the goal of eliminating jails.

10
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:52,210
When you believe, your mind finds ways to do.

11
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:55,330
This experiment has just one point.

12
00:00:55,600 --> 00:01:01,171
When you believe something is impossible, your mind goes to work for you to prove why.

13
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:10,210
But when you believe, really believe, something can be done, your mind goes to work for you and helps you find the ways to do it.

14
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:15,251
Believing something can be done paves the way for creative solutions.

15
00:01:15,441 --> 00:01:18,851
Believing something can't be done is destructive thinking.

16
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:22,851
This point applies to all situations, little and big.

17
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:34,371
The political leaders who do not genuinely believe permanent world peace can be established will fail because their minds are closed to creative ways to bring about peace.

18
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:42,451
The economists who believe business depressions are inevitable will not develop creative ways to beat the business cycle.

19
00:01:42,801 --> 00:01:48,770
In a similar fashion, you can find ways to like a person if you believe you can.

20
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:54,051
You can discover solutions to personal problems if you believe you can.

21
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:59,731
You can find a way to purchase that new larger home if you believe you can.

22
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:02,851
Belief releases creative powers.

23
00:02:03,201 --> 00:02:05,251
Disbelief puts the brakes on.

24
00:02:05,761 --> 00:02:09,491
Believe and you'll start thinking constructively.

25
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:15,411
Your mind will create a way if you let it.

